{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"520a6f99-f850-43e5-b11e-b663cbd02a36","content":"Here's my assessment — **not quite ready**. A few issues:\n\n**Critical / Functional:**\n- **`Framework` symbol has no `replaces`** — it defines a parameter but never substitutes it into project files. You likely need `\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"` (or a `TargetFramework` source name) so the chosen value actually gets written into the `.csproj`.\n\n**Recommended for NuGet publishing:**\n- **Missing `$schema`** — add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/editor support.\n- **Missing `groupIdentity`** — important so NuGet can group template versions together (e.g. `\"groupIdentity\": \"MyCompany.WebApi.CSharp\"`).\n- **Missing `precedence`** — helps the engine pick the right version when multiple are installed.\n\n**Nice to have:**\n- **No `defaultName`** — without it the generated project defaults to generic names. Consider `\"defaultName\": \"MyWebApi\"`.\n\nEverything else (`identity`, `shortName`, `sourceName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`) looks correct. Fix the `Framework` replaces issue and add `groupIdentity` before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9aab0acd-cfca-458c-b2e0-4d0e29fc3b5f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nKey issues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required, but recommended for validation and editor support.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet publishing so multiple versions of the same template can coexist.\n3. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but commonly set for project templates.\n4. **Missing `defaultName`** — The default project name when none is specified.\n5. **`Framework` symbol doesn't replace anything** — The symbol is defined but there's no `replaces` property to actually substitute the framework value in project files. This is a functional bug.\n\n\n6. **No `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the template are installed.\n\nThe most critical gaps for publishing are the missing `$schema` and `groupIdentity` fields, plus the `Framework` symbol that won't actually perform any substitutions since it lacks the `replaces` property.","outputTokens":569},"id":"fa3f1ad8-38ed-4aa6-9aea-c68fc6117aca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:22.115Z","parentId":"6ed5a17d-3972-41f1-98aa-7f18ed16ca56"}
